{
  "home": {
    "headings": [
      {
        "level": 1,
        "text": "Welcome to Mokosh Doula"
      },
      {
        "level": 1,
        "text": "My Services"
      },
      {
        "level": 3,
        "text": "Personalised Birth Support"
      },
      {
        "level": 3,
        "text": "Postpartum Care"
      },
      {
        "level": 3,
        "text": "Ceremonies Inspired by Ancient Wisdom"
      },
      {
        "level": 1,
        "text": "Connect with me"
      }
    ],
    "paragraphs": [
      "Mokosh is a revered figure in Slavic mythology, known for her deep connection to fertility, agriculture, and the well-being of families. As a goddess of the earth and protector of women, Mokosh embodies the nurturing, protective qualities that are at the heart of my doula services. Her legacy reminds me of the profound importance of support and care during one of life’s most pivotal moments.",
      "Inspired by Mokosh’s protective and nurturing qualities, I offer personalised support to ensure you feel empowered and cared for throughout your labour and birth. As your doula, I provide emotional support, practical assistance, and advocacy, helping to create a birth environment that aligns with your unique wishes and needs.",
      "Just as Mokosh nurtures and protects, I provide compassionate postpartum support to guide you through the transition into parenthood. From helping with infant care to offering emotional support and practical advice, my aim is to make this period as smooth and nurturing as possible for you and your family.",
      "At Mokosh Doula, I offer heartfelt ceremonies rooted in ancient traditions to honour the sacred transitions of motherhood. Drawing from Slavic heritage and timeless practices from around the world, these rituals celebrate the beauty, strength, and wisdom within you. From blessingways to postpartum closing ceremonies, each is carefully crafted to nurture your body, mind, and spirit. These ceremonies provide a meaningful way to honour your journey, weaving ancient wisdom into your modern birthing experience.",
      "I would love to meet you for tea and a chat to see if I’m the right doula for you.",
      "It is important to me that my services are accessible, so I am happy to be flexible with instalments and the duration of your payment plan. Please reach out if you would like to discuss about this further. ♥"
    ],
