  "about": {
    "headings": [
      {
        "level": 1,
        "text": "About me"
      },
      {
        "level": 2,
        "text": "Training & qualifications:"
      },
      {
        "level": 2,
        "text": "Here is what I do for fun"
      }
    ],
    "paragraphs": [
      "Hi, I’m Kat!",
      "I was born and raised in Poland. I grew up in a quiet, beautiful region surrounded by forests where wolves and bison still roam. Holistic care has been a part of my family for generations, passed down with wisdom and love.",
      "Doula care runs in my family—my great-grandmother was a  local traditional midwife, and my great-great-grandmother, a skilled herbalist, helped her daughter through a safe birth after multiple losses, inspiring my own path in supporting women through childbirth.",
      "Fifteen years ago, I moved to the UK to study management. That period was full of personal growth, self-discovery, and a lot of learning on the job as I worked my way up the career ladder. The Universe seemed to gently nudge me towards the world of pregnancy when I became a manager at a busy, private pregnancy clinic in London where I got valuable insight into pregnancy care, including ultrasound scans, blood tests, and maternity services.",
      "At the time, I didn’t realise the bigger plan unfolding—that this role was laying the foundation for my true calling as a doula.",
      "Everything became clear when I gave birth to my daughter at home. The experience was powerful, uplifting, and euphoric, awakening within me a profound calling to support women. From that moment, I knew my purpose was to help mothers feel confident and in tune with their natural power during pregnancy, birth, and beyond.",
      "“ Whenever and however you give birth, your experience will impact your emotions, your mind, your body, and your spirit for the rest of your life. ”",
      "~ Ina May Gaskin",
      "I’m deeply connected to the natural wisdom of women’s bodies and the incredible processes that Mother Nature guides us through. I believe a positive birth experience can really strengthen a woman’s trust in herself and her ability to be the mother she’s meant to be.",
      "My support is all about honouring your needs and wishes in labour and birth. As your doula, I’ll be by your side throughout the journey—offering guidance, being your advocate, listening closely, and creating a space where you can embrace your unique path. I provide continuous, personalised care from early pregnancy through postpartum, blending evidence-based practices with holistic tools like herbs, aromatherapy, homeopathy, grounding techniques, meditation, affirmations, and mindfulness.",
      "I’ll help you feel confident and empowered, ensuring you understand your options, your rights, and that no conversations happen without you. With me by your side, you can lean into your birth fully, letting your mind and body work together naturally. Birth is unforgettable, and my mission is to make sure your memories of it are beautiful.",
      "When I’m not supporting mums and their families, I love spending time with my own. In my downtime, you’ll usually find me cycling around London, exploring nature, or simply enjoying quiet moments to reconnect with the magic of the world around us."
    ],
